# ============================================================================
# Ivy Local Admin API Gateway — Complete Environment Configuration Template
# ============================================================================
# 
# This is a TEMPLATE file. Copy it to .env or .env.local and fill in your
# actual values. NEVER commit the .env file itself to version control.
#
# Setup Instructions:
#   1. cp .env.example .env.local
#   2. Edit .env.local with your actual credentials
#   3. Add to .gitignore: .env, .env.local, .env.*.local
#   4. For security, store sensitive values in:
#      - macOS Keychain (recommended for local dev)
#      - 1Password (for teams/production)
#      - AWS Secrets Manager (for cloud deployment)
#      - GitHub Secrets (for CI/CD workflows)
#
# Security Warning:
#   ⚠️  This file will contain sensitive API keys and credentials.
#   ⚠️  Keep .env out of version control (.gitignore)
#   ⚠️  Use restricted file permissions: chmod 600 .env.local
#   ⚠️  Only store on trusted, encrypted machines
#   ⚠️  Never share .env files via email, Slack, or unencrypted channels
#   ⚠️  If exposed, immediately rotate all credentials
#
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# SECTION 1: SECURITY & AUTHENTICATION
# ============================================================================

# Shared secret for protecting ALL FastAPI endpoints
# Used as X-API-Key header in requests (e.g., curl -H "X-API-Key: your_secret")
# CRITICAL: Change this to a random, secure value in production
# Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
ADMIN_SECRET=change_this_to_a_secure_random_key_in_production_12345

# Primary authorized contact phone number (Henry Hilla)
# Used for iMessage approval workflows and emergency notifications
# Format: +1 (country code) (area code) (number)
HENRY_PHONE=+12147334061

# ============================================================================
# SECTION 2: PRIMARY LLM ENGINES
# ============================================================================

# --- Google Gemini (PRIMARY) ---
# Primary AI conversation engine
# If this fails, the system automatically falls back to DeepSeek
#
# How to get the key:
#   1. Go to: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikeys
#   2. Create a new API key
#   3. Copy and paste below
#
# Rate limits: Free tier = 60 requests per minute
# Recommended model: gemini-2.5-flash (latest, fastest)
GEMINI_API_KEY=paste_your_gemini_api_key_here_from_makersuite

# --- DeepSeek API (FAILOVER) ---
# Failover AI engine - activates if Gemini is unavailable
# Provides similar capabilities but with different pricing/performance
#
# How to get the key:
#   1. Go to: https://platform.deepseek.com/api_keys
#   2. Sign up for a DeepSeek account (or log in)
#   3. Create a new API key
#   4. Copy and paste below
#
# Rate limits: Pay-per-use (no free tier)
# Recommended model: deepseek-chat
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=paste_your_deepseek_api_key_here_from_deepseek

# ============================================================================
# SECTION 3: LOCAL SYSTEM DATABASES & PATHS
# ============================================================================

# Path to your macOS iMessage chat database
# This is where Ivy polls for incoming messages from iMessage
# Default location: ~/Library/Messages/chat.db
# DO NOT EDIT unless you have a custom Messages storage location
CHAT_DB_PATH=/Users/lexi/Library/Messages/chat.db

# Optional: SQLite database for Ivy's internal state/caching
# Used to store polling state, cache results, etc.
# If not provided, Ivy uses in-memory storage (lost on restart)
STATE_DB_PATH=/Users/lexi/openclaw-admin/state.db

# ============================================================================
# SECTION 4: GROCERY STORE AUTOMATION
# ============================================================================

# --- H-E-B (H-E-B.COM) ---
# Credentials for automated grocery cart staging at H-E-B
# These are used by Playwright browser automation
# IMPORTANT: Use a dedicated account or enable 2FA bypass if needed
#
# To get credentials:
#   1. Create/use your H-E-B account at https://www.heb.com
#   2. Make sure account is verified and can log in from browser
#   3. Copy email and password below
#
# Security note: Consider using a separate account for automation
HEB_USERNAME=your_heb_email@example.com
HEB_PASSWORD=your_heb_password_here

# --- Kroger (KROGER.COM) ---
# Credentials for automated grocery cart staging at Kroger
# These are used by Playwright browser automation
#
# To get credentials:
#   1. Create/use your Kroger account at https://www.kroger.com
#   2. Make sure account is verified and can log in from browser
#   3. Copy email and password below
#
# Security note: Consider using a separate account for automation
KROGER_USERNAME=your_kroger_email@example.com
KROGER_PASSWORD=your_kroger_password_here

# ============================================================================
# SECTION 5: READWISE INTEGRATION (OPTIONAL)
# ============================================================================

# Readwise API token for fetching saved articles and highlights
# Used by the fetch_readwise_highlights() tool
# Leave blank if you don't use Readwise
#
# How to get the token:
#   1. Go to: https://readwise.io/access_token
#   2. Log in to your Readwise account
#   3. Copy the API token
#   4. Paste below
#
# This allows Ivy to access your saved articles for context/research
READWISE_API_KEY=paste_your_readwise_api_token_here_or_leave_blank

# ============================================================================
# SECTION 6: GOOGLE CLOUD PLATFORM (GCP) - OPTIONAL
# ============================================================================

# Path to your GCP Service Account JSON key file
# Used for Google Docs API, Google Sheets API, etc.
# Leave blank if not using GCP integrations
#
# How to get it:
#   1. Go to: https://console.cloud.google.com/iam-admin/serviceaccounts
#   2. Create a service account
#   3. Create a JSON key
#   4. Download and store securely
#   5. Point to the file below
#
# Security: NEVER commit the actual JSON file to GitHub
GCP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY_PATH=/Users/lexi/openclaw-admin/service-account-key.json

# Your GCP Project ID (for reference/debugging)
# Example: ai-gateway-v2-494905
GCP_PROJECT_ID=ai-gateway-v2-494905

# --- Google OAuth 2.0 (OPTIONAL) ---
# Refresh token for Google Docs/Sheets API access
# Used if you need to access your Google Drive documents
# Leave blank if not using Google Doc automation
GOOGLE_OAUTH_REFRESH_TOKEN=paste_your_google_oauth_refresh_token_here_or_leave_blank

# Google Drive Folder ID for storing/accessing Docs
# Used to organize generated documents in a specific Drive folder
# Leave blank to use root Drive directory
GOOGLE_DOCS_FOLDER_ID=your_google_drive_folder_id_or_leave_blank

# ============================================================================
# SECTION 7: DATABASE CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================

# Polling interval: How often (in seconds) to check iMessage database
# Lower = more responsive but higher CPU usage
# Default: 1 second (recommended for local dev)
# For production: 2-5 seconds is often sufficient
POLLING_INTERVAL=1

# SQLite database connection timeout (in seconds)
# Time to wait before giving up on a database read
# Default: 5 seconds (reasonable for local macOS)
DB_TIMEOUT=5

# Database retry attempts before giving up
# How many times to retry if database read fails
# Default: 3 attempts with exponential backoff
DB_RETRY_ATTEMPTS=3

# ============================================================================
# SECTION 8: API TIMEOUTS & RATE LIMITING
# ============================================================================

# External API timeout (in seconds)
# Applies to calls to:
#   - Readwise API
#   - DeepSeek API
#   - Google APIs
# Default: 20 seconds (reasonable for most services)
EXTERNAL_API_TIMEOUT=20

# API rate limiting: Max requests per minute
# Currently not enforced but reserved for future use
# Default: 100 requests/minute
API_RATE_LIMIT=100

# ============================================================================
# SECTION 9: PLAYWRIGHT BROWSER AUTOMATION (GROCERY STAGING)
# ============================================================================

# Enable/disable Playwright browser automation
# Set to 'false' to completely disable /stage_groceries endpoint
# Default: true
PLAYWRIGHT_ENABLED=true

# Run Playwright in headless mode (no visible browser window)
# Set to 'false' to see the browser window (useful for debugging)
# Default: true (headless)
# Note: If false, you'll see the browser visually adding items to cart
PLAYWRIGHT_HEADLESS=true

# ============================================================================
# SECTION 10: FEATURE FLAGS (ENABLE/DISABLE FEATURES)
# ============================================================================

# These allow you to enable/disable specific features without code changes
# All default to true; set to false to disable

# Enable iMessage polling background thread
# If false, Ivy won't listen for incoming iMessages
# Default: true
ENABLE_IMESSAGE_POLLER=true

# Enable grocery staging at H-E-B and Kroger
# If false, /stage_groceries endpoint will return 503 (unavailable)
# Default: true
ENABLE_GROCERY_STAGING=true

# Enable Apple Calendar integration
# If false, check_apple_calendar tool will not work
# Default: true
ENABLE_CALENDAR_INTEGRATION=true

# Enable Apple Reminders integration
# If false, add_apple_reminder and fetch_apple_reminders tools won't work
# Default: true
ENABLE_REMINDERS_INTEGRATION=true

# Enable Readwise integration
# If false, fetch_readwise_highlights tool won't work
# Default: true (but requires READWISE_API_KEY to be set)
ENABLE_READWISE_INTEGRATION=true

# ============================================================================
# SECTION 11: LOGGING & DEBUGGING
# ============================================================================

# Logging level for Ivy's output
# Options:
#   DEBUG    = Very verbose (all operations logged, including secrets sanitized)
#   INFO     = Standard (important events and milestones)
#   WARNING  = Warnings only (when features are unavailable or degraded)
#   ERROR    = Errors only (when operations fail)
#   CRITICAL = Critical failures only (system-level issues)
# Default: INFO (recommended)
LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# ============================================================================
# SECTION 12: MCP (MODEL CONTEXT PROTOCOL) - ADVANCED/OPTIONAL
# ============================================================================

# If using external MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers
# MCP allows connecting to external AI tools and services
# Leave blank if not using MCP

# Command to start MCP server (e.g., "python /path/to/mcp_server.py")
MCP_SERVER_COMMAND=/path/to/mcp/server/executable

# Command-line arguments for MCP server
MCP_SERVER_ARGS=--arg1 value1 --arg2 value2

# Working directory for MCP server process
MCP_SERVER_CWD=/path/to/mcp/server/working/directory

# ============================================================================
# SECTION 13: ADVANCED CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================

# Playwright timeout for browser operations (in milliseconds)
# How long to wait for Playwright to find/click elements
# Default: 10000 ms (10 seconds, set in config.py)
# (Note: This is set in config.py, not here)

# ============================================================================
# QUICK REFERENCE: WHERE TO GET EACH SECRET
# ============================================================================
#
# API Key / Credential           | Where to Get It
# -------------------------------|----------------------------------------------
# GEMINI_API_KEY                 | https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikeys
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY               | https://platform.deepseek.com/api_keys
# READWISE_API_KEY               | https://readwise.io/access_token
# HEB_USERNAME/PASSWORD          | Your H-E-B account (https://www.heb.com)
# KROGER_USERNAME/PASSWORD       | Your Kroger account (https://www.kroger.com)
# GCP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY_PATH   | https://console.cloud.google.com/iam-admin/serviceaccounts
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_REFRESH_TOKEN     | https://myaccount.google.com/permissions
# HENRY_PHONE                    | Known contact (already filled in as example)
# ADMIN_SECRET                   | Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
#
# ============================================================================
# COMMON SETUP WORKFLOWS
# ============================================================================
#
# WORKFLOW 1: Local Development (Minimal Setup)
#   - Fill in: GEMINI_API_KEY, DEEPSEEK_API_KEY
#   - Fill in: HEB_USERNAME/PASSWORD (if using grocery staging)
#   - Leave blank: Everything else (will use defaults)
#   - Save as: .env.local
#
# WORKFLOW 2: Full Local Development
#   - Fill in: All API keys and credentials you plan to use
#   - Set feature flags: ENABLE_* = true for features you want
#   - Save as: .env.local
#
# WORKFLOW 3: Production Deployment
#   - Store secrets in: AWS Secrets Manager or 1Password
#   - Do NOT create .env file
#   - Load secrets from secure manager on startup
#   - Set LOG_LEVEL: WARNING
#
# ============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================================================
#
# Error: "GEMINI_API_KEY missing from environment vars"
#   → Make sure GEMINI_API_KEY is set in .env.local
#   → Run: export GEMINI_API_KEY="your_key"
#
# Error: "Playwright not installed — /stage_groceries will be unavailable"
#   → Run: pip install playwright
#   → Run: playwright install chromium
#
# Error: "Cannot access chat.db files. Verify Full Disk Access"
#   → Go to System Preferences → Security & Privacy → Full Disk Access
#   → Add Terminal/Python/IDE you're using
#
# Error: "X-API-Key header missing or invalid"
#   → Add header to request: -H "X-API-Key: your_admin_secret"
#
# ============================================================================
# NEXT STEPS
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy this file:
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#
# 2. Edit with your credentials:
#    nano .env.local
#    or
#    vim .env.local
#
# 3. Make sure .env.local is in .gitignore:
#    echo ".env.local" >> .gitignore
#    git add .gitignore
#    git commit -m "chore: add .env.local to gitignore"
#
# 4. Test the gateway:
#    python main.py
#
# 5. Test an endpoint:
#    curl -X GET http://localhost:8000/health \
#      -H "X-API-Key: your_admin_secret"
#
# ============================================================================
